Cost Drivers & Shop Considerations\par
\par
PEEK Material Costs:\par
\par
Virgin PEEK is the primary cost driver for the Main Mandrel due to the requirement for an 8.000" length and 1.7500" OD.\par
While expensive, it is necessary to ensure the 0.0637" (1.618 mm) pitch does not drift during operation.\par
\par
Chassis Fabrication (G10 Garolite):\par
\par
The 10.000" x 14.000" x 1.000" plate size for the Box-Beam chassis requires high-pressure laminate.\par
 Because G10 is highly abrasive, the cost includes a "Tooling Tax" for PCD (Polycrystalline Diamond) or high-quality carbide bits that won't dull mid-cut.\par
\par
Magnetic & Hardware Precision:\par
\par
The 800 lb (3.55\\kN) repulsion force requires high-grade N52 magnets.\par
 Standard fasteners are insufficient; you must verify that the 3/8-16 Stainless (316) bolts are truly non-magnetic to avoid interfering with the 25 MHz phase.\par
\par
\par
For the \b Stage 2 Intermediate Functional Prototype the total cost \b0 is divided between raw materials, specialized high-frequency wiring, and the "Tooling Tax" required to machine high-performance polymers and laminates to Red Seal tolerances.\par
\par
