The "Master Engineer" Financial Strategy\par
Because this prototype is destined for SR&ED (Scientific Research & Experimental Development), the actual "net cost" to Galalith Bioplastics Inc. is significantly lower:\par
\par
1.  Immediate Tax Deduction: The full $3,380 is a 100% current year expense.\par
2.  Refundable Tax Credit: At a 35% SR&ED rate, you would receive approximately $1,183 back as a cash refund from the CRA.\par
How the $1,183 Cash is GeneratedIf your Stage 2 prototype costs $3,380 in qualified materials (PEEK, Silver, G10, etc.):Deduction: \par
You deduct the $3,380 from your income (reducing any tax you might eventually owe).\par
Credit Calculation: $3,380 \f0\lang1033 x\f1\lang9  35% = $1,183.The "Cash" Phase: Because you are a CCPC developing the XTP-1 and likely have more expenses than revenue during this R&D phase, the CRA processes the $1,183 as a refund.\par
3.  Net Effective Cost: Approximately $2,197 for a fully documented, high-purity synthesis asset.\par
\par
Metrology & Inspection:\par
\par
 While not a direct material cost, the setup requires a Dial Test Indicator capable of measuring < 0.0002" bore runout.\par
 A Profilometer is needed to confirm the 16 Ra (0.4 \f2\lang1032\'ecm) finish on the internal bore to protect the substrate interface.\par
